<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  com.sma.daemon.plist — the macOS launchd LaunchAgent that supervises the SMA V5
  daemon on the first 24/7 host, the Mac mini (D-9.5-02b). This is the thin
  supervisor layer ONLY (D-9.5-02a): the daemon process itself is host-agnostic;
  launchd binds it to macOS, exactly as sma-daemon-windows.task.xml binds it to the
  Windows Task Scheduler and a systemd unit would bind it to Linux. All three are
  add-only siblings over the SAME host-neutral core.

  WHY LaunchAgent, NOT LaunchDaemon (portability audit rows 10/11; assumptions A2/A7)
    A LaunchDaemon runs at boot with NO user context and NO login session. The daemon
    spawns `claude` / `codex` workers whose auth is strictly PER-USER: `claude
    setup-token` credentials, `~/.claude`, and each account's CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR all
    live under the worker user. A background LaunchDaemon may also be denied Keychain
    access. So the 24/7 shape is a LaunchAgent under a DEDICATED auto-login worker
    user: the mini logs that user in automatically at boot, launchd loads this agent
    at login (RunAtLoad), and the per-user auth is present. Keychain-vs-headless is
    verified live during setup-macos.md; if OAuth-in-Keychain proves to work headless,
    the token env files can be simplified later.

  PLACEHOLDER CONVENTION (fill BEFORE `launchctl load`, same as the Windows harness)
    <SMA_HOME>     absolute path of the mini's ../sma clone
                   (e.g. /Users/worker/sma). The daemon composition root is
                   <SMA_HOME>/daemon/src/main.mjs.
    <WORKER_HOME>  the auto-login worker user's home dir (e.g. /Users/worker).
                   launchd does NOT expand `~`, so the log paths must be absolute.
    Node path: Apple Silicon Homebrew installs node at /opt/homebrew/bin/node
    (used below). On an Intel Mac mini it is /usr/local/bin/node — swap if needed.
    Confirm with `which node` during setup.

  ProgramArguments targets main.mjs — the composition root from plan 9.5-08 task 4.
  It wires config -> durable queue -> event hub -> event-wrapped adapter into BOTH the
  stateless tick AND the roster front (one process, one adapter). The 9.5-RESEARCH
  launchd example still named loop.mjs; that reference predates the D-9.5-05 РЕВИЗИЯ
  entrypoint. main.mjs is the correct target — loop.mjs is a library the root imports.

  KeepAlive true = launchd restarts the process on any exit (crash, kill, OOM). Combined
  with the daemon's statelessness (D-9.5-02: all truth in Postgres + .sma/ + git), a
  restart resumes losslessly — this is the macOS half of the kill-drill proven in the
  bring-up pass (plan 9.5-10 task 3).

  INSTALL (founder, per setup-macos.md):
    cp supervisor/com.sma.daemon.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.sma.daemon.plist
    # edit the two placeholders in the copy, then:
    launchctl load -w ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.sma.daemon.plist
    launchctl list | grep com.sma.daemon      # confirm it is running
  UNLOAD:
    launchctl unload -w ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.sma.daemon.plist
-->
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.sma.daemon</string>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
      <string>/opt/homebrew/bin/node</string>
      <string>&lt;SMA_HOME&gt;/daemon/src/main.mjs</string>
    </array>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <true/>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>&lt;WORKER_HOME&gt;/Library/Logs/sma-daemon.log</string>

    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>&lt;WORKER_HOME&gt;/Library/Logs/sma-daemon.err</string>

    <key>ProcessType</key>
    <string>Background</string>

    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
    <string>&lt;SMA_HOME&gt;</string>
  </dict>
</plist>
